description:
&lt;p&gt;Community Registered NurseAre you self-motivated, enthusiastic and looking for a new challenge?Would you like the opportunity to develop your nursing career in the community setting? We deliver care from 8am-9pm seven days a week including weekends and bank holidays working different shifts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a compassionate, hardworking and motivated registered nurse to join our District Nursing Team in Central Southend/Shoeburyness.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have daily responsibility for providing care to patients within the community setting. You will liaise closely with local GP&#39;s and other members of the wider MDT as well as with patients and their families, therefore excellent communication skills are essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are opportunities for further professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be a first level registered nurse, hold a full valid driving licence and have access to a car.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Season Ticket Loans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discounts for staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent Training facilities and opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to work bank shifts and expand knowledge and experience in other areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary Sacrifice schemes including lease cars and Cycle to Work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Buying and Selling annual leave scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mandy Burgess&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;amanda.burgess@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
